<skill name="contextManagement">
Use this skill when working with long conversations, large files, or extended projects.

Preserve important decisions, constraints, and completed work.
Avoid repeatedly loading or repeating identical information.

When context becomes large:
- summarize completed steps
- keep important technical details
- discard redundant or low-value information
- preserve user requirements and project structure

Prefer reading only the relevant portions of files instead of entire large files whenever possible.

When modifying existing work:
- maintain consistency with earlier decisions
- avoid contradicting previous changes
- track unfinished tasks and known issues

If information is uncertain because of missing context, gather the missing information before proceeding.
</skill>